<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-146-073 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 775 224</DOCID><JOURNAL>San Jose Mercury News  May 30 1991 p1F(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apple to reorganize U.S. sales and marketing unit.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wolf, Ron; Oppenheimer-Pitthan, Cris.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple Computer Inc begins a reorganization of Apple USA on May 31,1991.andP;  The restructure of the computer maker's sales and marketingunit is seen as a part of general cost reductions.andP;  Apple plans toeliminate 1,500 jobs throughout the company, with many of the cutsexpected to come from the sales and marketing operations aroundthe country and from its corporate headquarters in Cupertino, CA.andO;Few of the cuts are expected to come from its manufacturing plantsor its research and development divisions.andP;  Apple plans toconsolidate the five regional sales divisions into three regionaldivisions with headquarters in New York, Atlanta and Irvine, CA.andO;This eliminates Apple USA's northwest regional headquarters in SanJose, CA and its central regional headquarters in Chicago.andP;  AppleUSA plans on a new reseller operations group in San Jose to managenational accounts.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (Personnel management)Apple USA (Management).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Topic:     ReorganizationSalesMarketingManufacturingResearch and DevelopmentValue-Added Resellers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>